# BROWSER-core.md - Medium Global Rules, Shared Patterns & Selectors


---

## § 2. Read Article Content + Clap (combined — ONE evaluate)

Reads article content AND claps 5x in a single evaluate. Saves one step per article.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); const h1 = document.querySelector('h1'); const article = document.querySelector('article'); const content = article ? article.innerText : document.body.innerText; const lines = content.split(String.fromCharCode(10)).filter(l => l.trim()); const contentStart = lines.findIndex(l => l.length > 80); const body = contentStart >= 0 ? lines.slice(contentStart).join(String.fromCharCode(10)) : content; const btn = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"headerClapButton\"]'); var clapped = 0; if (btn) { for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) { btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mousedown', { bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50)); btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseup', { bubbles: true })); btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); } clapped = 5; } return { title: h1 ? h1.innerText : '', content: body.slice(0, 1200), clapped: clapped }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
🚨 Use `article` element — NOT `document.body.innerText` (includes sidebar/nav junk).
🚨 mousedown→50ms→mouseup→click→500ms per clap. Without delays, rapid-fire triggers hold-to-clap (50 instead of 5).

