## § 3. Write Response (Inline Editor)

🚨 **Uses the INLINE editor at the bottom of the article page — NOT the dialog.** The dialog editor has intermittent Slate state bugs where the Respond button stays disabled. The inline editor is reliable.
🚨 **Submit buttons:** Use `dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', ...))` — NOT `.click()`.
🚨 **Response text escaping:** ALWAYS use double-quoted strings or `JSON.stringify()` for response text in evaluate. Single quotes break on apostrophes (e.g. "it's", "don't") → `Invalid or unexpected token`.
🚨 **NEVER use the dialog** (`div[role="dialog"]`) for typing responses. NEVER open the responses panel before typing.
🚨 **Medium 500 errors:** Submitting a response often triggers a server-side 500 error that crashes the page. **The response IS saved despite the 500.** The verify step (Step 2) handles this by reloading and checking the responses panel.
🚨 **Slate text persistence:** Medium's Slate.js editor persists typed text across page reloads via localStorage. ALWAYS clear the editor before typing to prevent text duplication on retries.

**Step 1a — Scroll to editor, clear, type (evaluate ~800 chars):**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var dialog = document.querySelector('div[role=\"dialog\"]'); var allTb = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div[contenteditable=\"true\"][role=\"textbox\"]')); var tb = allTb.find(function(el) { return !dialog || !dialog.contains(el); }); if (!tb) return { error: 'no inline textbox found' }; tb.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll'); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var text = window.__data.text; tb.focus(); var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', text); tb.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('beforeinput', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); return { typed: true, len: tb.innerText.length }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_RESPONSE_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 1b — Find Respond button + submit (evaluate ~500 chars):**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var btn = null; for (var attempt = 0; attempt < 5; attempt++) { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var dialog = document.querySelector('div[role=\"dialog\"]'); var allBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); btn = allBtns.find(function(b) { return (!dialog || !dialog.contains(b)) && b.innerText.trim() === 'Respond' && !b.disabled; }); if (btn) break; btn = null; } if (!btn) return { error: 'no Respond button' }; btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); return { submitted: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
🚨 Whether Step 1b returns `submitted: true` OR `error: 'no Respond button'` → **ALWAYS proceed to Step 2 (verify)**. Medium often saves the response even when the button isn't found.
🚨 **Medium 500s after EVERY submit.** Do NOT check the current page. Navigate to the article URL directly.

**Step 2 — Navigate to article + verify (ONE evaluate, handles 500 automatically):**

After submit, page ALWAYS 500s — response IS saved. Navigate back to article URL and check responses panel in one call.

**Before calling Step 2:** navigate to the ORIGINAL article URL (not the response post URL). Wait 5s.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"{articleUrl}"}' 2>&1
```

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5000)); window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var seeAll = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.includes('See all'); }); if (seeAll) { seeAll.click(); } else { var countBtn = btns.find(function(b) { var n = parseInt(b.innerText.trim()); return n > 0 && n < 500 && b.innerText.trim().length <= 3; }); if (countBtn) countBtn.click(); } await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var snippet = window.__data.snippet; var dialog = document.querySelector('div[role=\"dialog\"]'); if (dialog && dialog.innerText.includes(snippet)) return { verified: true }; var hasOurText = document.body.innerText.includes(snippet); var hasOurName = document.body.innerText.includes('{{name}}') || document.body.innerText.includes('{{display_name}}'); return { verified: hasOurText && hasOurName, fallback: true }; }", "data": {"snippet": "first 40 chars of response"}}
ENDJSON
```

🚨 If `verified: true` → success, proceed to tracking.
🚨 If `verified: false` → response was likely NOT posted. Retry Step 1 once (with clear). Max 1 retry → skip article.
🚨 **Total steps per response: Step 1 (type+submit) + navigate + Step 2 (verify) = 3 steps.** NOT 8-13 steps with 500 reload loops.

