## Selectors Reference

### Notifications Page
- Container: `div[role="tabpanel"]`, items: direct children
- Type detection: "responded"=response, "left a note"=note (only actionable types)
- Article URL: `a[href*="/p/"]`
- Author name: `n.innerText.split('\n')[0]`

### Article Page (browse_and_engage dedup ONLY)
- Our comment: `a[href*="/@{{handle_slug}}"]` filtered by `.filter(a => !a.href.includes('sidebar_menu'))` count > 0
- Secondary: `/\nYou\n\n\d+\s+(mins?|hours?|days?)\s+ago/` on body text
- ❌ **NEVER use this for notification replies** — our original comment's `/@{{handle_slug}}` link always causes false positives on response pages (tested 2026-02-19: 4/4 false positives). Use tracking file dedup only.

### Editor (Inline Slate.js — NOT dialog)
- Selector: `div[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]` — pick the one NOT inside `div[role="dialog"]`
- DOM signature: `data-slate-node`, `data-slate-leaf`, `data-slate-string` attributes
- Submit: button text "Respond" ONLY (NOT "Reply" — those are for comment threads) — pick the one NOT inside `div[role="dialog"]`
- ✅ Atomic clear+type+submit (§ 3 Step 1): scroll to bottom → **clear editor** → focus → paste → InputEvent → **retry loop (5x 1000ms, re-query dialog)** → submit — ALL in one async evaluate
- Clear editor before typing (`selectAll` + `delete` + InputEvent) — Slate persists text in localStorage
- Use `JSON.stringify(text)` for response text (handles apostrophes, quotes, newlines)
- Dispatch `InputEvent('input', { inputType: 'insertText' })` after typing — syncs Slate state
- Retry Respond button detection (5x, 1000ms gaps) with re-queried dialog ref after InputEvent
- Verify via responses panel (§ 3 Step 2)

### Clap Button
- `button[data-testid="headerClapButton"]`
- Batch evaluate: mousedown+mouseup+click loop

### Follow Button
- `querySelectorAll('button')` → find text "Follow"
- `.click()` works for follow

### Search Results
- Container: `article` elements
- Title: `h2, h3` inside article
- ✅ Both `/@author/` and publication URLs accepted (regex: `/medium\.com\/((@[^/]+)|([^@][^/]+))\/[^/]+-[a-f0-9]{8,}/`)
- Publication URLs may redirect to custom domains — this works. If SSL error → skip immediately.

### General
- Reliable: `role` attributes, element tags, text content
- Unreliable: class names (obfuscated)

---

## Recovery

- **Browser timeout** → close + reopen. If fails → restart via `/start` endpoint, wait 3s, retry once.
- **Unexpected data** → check URL, re-navigate if wrong page.
- **Editor typing fails** → reload page, wait 5s, retry § 3 Step 1 once. Max 1 retry → skip.
- **Respond button not found OR page 500 after submit** → both are NORMAL. Navigate to the original article URL, wait 5s, run § 3 Step 2 (verify). The response is almost always saved. Do NOT reload the 500 page — navigate to the article instead. If not verified → retry Step 1 once. Max 1 retry → skip.
- 🚨 **Do NOT loop on 500 pages** — each reload+check costs 2 steps. Navigate away from the 500 page immediately.
- **SSL error** → skip URL immediately. NEVER retry.
